comments.api-context:
If you have a need to use the storage context for createApi.
    You can do it here using the example below.

    https://redux-toolkit.js.org/rtk-query/usage/customizing-create-api

    Example:

    import { createDispatchHook, createSelectorHook, createStoreHook } from 'react-redux';

    export const createApi = buildCreateApi(
        coreModule(),
        reactHooksModule({
            useDispatch: createDispatchHook(context),
            useSelector: createSelectorHook(context),
            useStore   : createStoreHook(context)
        })
    );
